RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Bred Futurity Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 1 350 Y Dirt CR: 74. Futurity Trial Purse 8000. A FUTURITY TRIAL FOR ACCREDITED ALBERTA BRED TWO-YEAR-OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE ALBERTA BRED FUTURITY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS FANCY NANCY won handily under a confident ride. GET IT GOOD drifted out leaving the chute and was outfinished. HEZ HOTT UR NOTT missed late. MOUNTAIN NIGHT TRAIN bid belatedly. CAPES TIMBER brushed leaving and raced evenly. NOT EASY BEING ME steadied leaving and failed to make an impression.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: O LETS BE FIRST edged clear late. HORTONS TRUTH caught late. EYE M bumped away from gate and rallied late. ST PADDY 109 jostled leaving and was outrun. MONTANA CHICK bumped inside rival and came up empty in drive. BELLAWAVE shifted outside and lacked a bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Bred Futurity Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 3 350 Y Dirt CR: 80. Futurity Trial Purse 8000. A FUTURITY TRIAL FOR ACCREDITED ALBERTA BRED TWO-YEAR-OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE ALBERTA BRED FUTURITY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BITTERROOTS WAGON just held under a drive. DJ BRIGHT RUBY dug in late getting up for place. MS MINI WARRIOR narrowly denied. WINKINS WAGON BOSS weakened in final yards. NORTHFORK THREE TEN gave best late. TIMBERS BEAUTY was fractious and was outrun throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Bred Maturity S. CENTURY DOWNS RACE 4 350 Y Dirt CR: 74. Match Race Purse 21000. A STAKES RACE FOR THREE YEAR OLD & UPWARD ACCREDITED ALBERTA BRED QUARTER HORSES. Time of Entry $200. Preferences as per the AQHRA. Weight 124 lbs 3 Year Old, 126 lbs Older.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOUBLE CRUISE gained the lead leaving the chute and held safely. TIMBERS EXPRESS closed late and got up for second. INSEPERABLE COWGIRL lacked rally needed. BEARCAT BILL broke in bumping into TIMBERS MOON and failed to threaten. TIMBERS MOON bumped hard leaving, and retreated. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Board of Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start. After review, it was determined that BEARCAT BILL caused interference with TIMBERS MOON leaving the gate. BEARCAT BILL was disqualified and placed fifth.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Bred Derby Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 5 400 Y Dirt CR: 70. Derby Trial Purse 8000. A DERBY TRIAL FOR ACCREDITED ALBERTA BRED THREE-YEAR-OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE ALBERTA BRED DERBY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEZA MAJESTIC HERO broke out leaving, responded gamely to urging and won driving. APPRECIATE flashed early speed and was caught late. FDD FAST MAN bumped away, and rallied late. JAMEZ BOND bumped leaving, rallied outside, and missed. TIMBER BUNNY broke in sharply and trailed. TRAINER OBJECTION- An objection was called by the trainer of FDD FAST MAN alleging interference against the rider of HEZA MAJESTIC HERO away from the gate was disallowed after review of the Stewards.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Bred Derby Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 6 400 Y Dirt CR: 73. Derby Trial Purse 8000. A DERBY TRIAL FOR ACCREDITED ALBERTA BRED THREE-YEAR-OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE ALBERTA BRED DERBY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUNK DRAWER rallied three wide and edged away late. NORTHFORK BOSS rallied inside and weakened in the final yards. TULSA TIMBER needed more late. EYEMADASHIN showed interest late. SPRINGELEER outrun throughout.

ENTRY.NAME: Northfork Boss
ENTRY.OWNER: Wills Glenn Stockwell Buckey A and Gehring Delton D

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CTHS Sales S. CENTURY DOWNS RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 72. Stakes Purse 100000. A SALE STAKE FOR TWO YEAR OLD CANADIAN BREDS. Any Canadian bred yearling that passed through the CTHS Alberta Division sales ring a buyer's fee of $200 over and above the purchase price of the yearling must be paid by the purchaser at the time of sale in order to be eligible for the 2023 2YO restricted Sales Stake. Qualifying CTHS Alberta Sale graduates have at minimum 5 guaranteed entries for the race are free to nominate, $500 to enter and $500 to start. Any Canadian bred that passed through the CTHS ( MB), CTHS (BC) or CTHS (ON) sales ring is also eligible provided that the $750 nomination fee is paid at the time of nomination, the $750 entry fee to pass the entry box and $1,000 to start is paid. AB Sales Graduates are Preferred. Second preference is g iven by earnings in 2023. Field limited to Ten Starters and four also eligible. Purse distribution: 1st- 60%, 2nd- 20%, 3rd -10%, 4th- 3.5%, 5th- 2.5%, 6th- 2%, Consignor of winning horse- 2%.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ITSALLGOODMAN quickly took command, held good margins through the backstretch, rider peered underarm then geared down when uncovered. JUMP THE QUEUE stalked the early pace from the three path, raced in closest pursuit, was no match for the winner, and held safely for second. B B'S WILDFIRE rated from off-the-pace between foes, dropped back in the final turn, and finished evenly. SILKSTONE trailed early and showed a mild interest late. JODEYS LIL PAIN saved ground and was done early.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 (AB $5,000) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Cl aiming Price $8,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMILIN EVIE brushed outside rival leaving, vied for the early lead then emerged the leader entering the backstretch, turned back a challenge from BOOTIFUL ROSE into the final turn, and drew clear. DIXIE MO broke outward leaving, gained closer order outside through the backstretch, drove four to five wide at the head of the lane, and was along in time for second place. BOOTIFUL ROSE brushed away from the gate, vied in the two path, sat just off the pace, loomed boldly nearing the final turn, was unable to get by the eventual winner, and was caught late. LITTLE HARPER lacked running room leaving the chute, trailed early, lodged a rail bid while advancing quickly nearing the stretch then flattened. THRILL OF THE NITE attended the pace while three wide, and came up empty late. EYESPYMYLITTLEEYE vied four wide into the opening turn, and was outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Smilin Evie
ENTRY.OWNER: Clark Ann and Clary Robert A

ENTRY.NAME: Bootiful Rose
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed, vied, loomed boldly, caught late

ENTRY.NAME: Little Harper
ENTRY.COMMENT: lacked room, trailed, bid inside, flattened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 9 7F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 35000. FOR ALBERTA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WISH ON A STAR contested the early pace outside of BUSTER BRADY, inherited the lead leaving the backstretch, opened up to good margins, and stayed clear under light handling. BRYNN'S DREAM reserved off the early pacesetters, lodged an all-out bid into the stretch but was no match for the winner, and finished second-best. OUR SUNSHINE unhurried early, gained closer order under encouragement, and finished with good energy. ALBERTA BERBON trailed early, chased through the far turn, and was outkicked. KISS ME HELLO chased the pacesetters through the backstretch, moved up menacingly in the far turn, but had nothing left in reserve. SMOKIN JOY outsprinted through the opening turn and was outrun. BUSTER BRADY contended the early pace from the rail, was unable to move on with the eventual winner, and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Our Sunshine
ENTRY.OWNER: Goldbeck, Ernest D. and Ilene A.
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, gained, finished good energy

ENTRY.NAME: Brynn's Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, all out bid, finished 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 10 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHERE'S THE GOLD raced near the back of the pack early, circled the field into the lane, and narrowly prevailed after a multi-horse scramble to the wire. WALKTHELINE stalked the pace from the rail, lacked running room in the final turn, angled in sharply when a seam appeared, gained a slim advantage, and was narrowly denied. TOOL TIME set the pace from the two path, was under attack into the final turn, and was worn down late finishing on the wire for third at the same time as MOUNT ASGARD. MOUNT ASGARD sat just off the pace from the three path, pressed the issue in the final turn, rallied determinedly through the stretch, and finished third best on the wire with TOOL TIME. SAXON SAGA tracked the pace from the three path, rallied four to five wide in the final turn, and gave way late stretch. *Photo Finish Malfunction- The order of finish was determined by the Board of Stewards.

ENTRY.NAME: Where's the Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: back of pack, circled, narrowly prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: Walktheline
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, lacked room, narrowly denied

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Mount Asgard
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3w, pressured, rallied determinedly, 3rd best, DH

FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 (AB $5,000) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 . Alberta Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BACKSTREET BOBBY stalked the pace from the rail, shifted outside into the final turn, rallied gradually through the stretch, and inched clear. COMMON KNOWLEDGE broke alertly to set the pace, showed the way through the backstretch, and was worn down late. EXAMINER sat midpack, angled down to the rail at the head of the stretch, and improved position late. BIG AL'S VISION raced three to four wide into the opening turn, and lacked a closing response that was needed. LIFESBEENGOODSOFAR trailed early, and lodged a late mild bid. DUNE D'ORO stumbled after the start, and lacked a serious bid. ISLE OF SKYE offered little. PUMP THE BRAKES chased the pace from the three path, and yielded into stretch.
